cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with the task of semantic segmentation. It also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which makes it relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach for similarity-based guidance, which could be of interest to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) community. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on the Pascal VOC 2012 dataset, which is commonly used in Multimedia (cs.MM) research.
